            <h4>Step 2: Determine the Asar Altitude (ZA)</h4>
            <p>The altitude of the Sun at Asar is derived from the shadow length. First, the zenith angle of the Sun at Zuhr is corrected for refraction, then the shadow factor is applied.</p>
            
            <p><strong> ZA<sub>hz</sub> = φ - δ - SD</strong><br>
            = ${fmt(F11)} - ${fmt(sun_zuhr.dec)} - ${fmt(sun_zuhr.sd,6)}<br>
            = <strong>${fmt(ZA_hz)}°</strong></p>
            
            <p><strong> Refraction correction for Zuhr altitude:</strong><br>
            R<sub>hm</sub> = 0.017 × tan(ZA<sub>hz</sub> - 10.3/(95.11 - ZA<sub>hz</sub>))<br>
            = 0.017 × tan(${fmt(ZA_hz)} - ${(10.3/(95.11 - ZA_hz)).toFixed(4)})<br>
            = 0.017 × tan(${fmt(ZA_hz - 10.3/(95.11 - ZA_hz))})<br>
            = <strong>${fmt(R_hm,6)}°</strong></p>
            
            <p><strong> Corrected ZA<sub>hmz</sub> = ZA<sub>hz</sub> - R<sub>hm</sub></strong><br>
            = ${fmt(ZA_hz)} - ${fmt(R_hm,6)} = <strong>${fmt(ZA_hmz)}°</strong></p>
            
            <p><strong> Apply shadow factor (${asrFactor}):</strong><br>
            tan(ZA<sub>hma</sub>) = tan(ZA<sub>hmz</sub>) + ${asrFactor}<br>
            = ${fmt(tand(ZA_hmz))} + ${asrFactor} = ${fmt(tand(ZA_hmz) + asrFactor)}<br>
            ZA<sub>hma</sub> = arctan(${fmt(tand(ZA_hmz) + asrFactor)}) = <strong>${fmt(ZA_hma)}°</strong></p>
            
            <p><strong> Refraction correction for Asar altitude:</strong><br>
            R<sub>mh</sub> = (P/1010) × (283/(273+T)) × 0.0167 × tan(ZA<sub>hma</sub> - 7.31/(94.4 - ZA<sub>hma</sub>))<br>
            = (${pressure}/1010) × (283/(273+${temp})) × 0.0167 × tan(${fmt(ZA_hma)} - ${(7.31/(94.4 - ZA_hma)).toFixed(4)})<br>
            = ${(pressure/1010).toFixed(4)} × ${(283/(273+temp)).toFixed(4)} × 0.0167 × tan(${fmt(ZA_hma - 7.31/(94.4 - ZA_hma))})<br>
            = <strong>${fmt(R_mh,6)}°</strong></p>
            
            <p><strong> Final zenith angle for Asar:</strong><br>
            ZA<sub>asar</sub> = ZA<sub>hma</sub> + R<sub>mh</sub> + SD<br>
            = ${fmt(ZA_hma)} + ${fmt(R_mh,6)} + ${fmt(sun_zuhr.sd,6)}<br>
            = <strong>${fmt(ZA_asar)}°</strong></p>
            
            <h4>Step 3: Compute Hour Angle (H) Using Spherical Trigonometry</h4>
            <p class="formula">cos H = [cos(ZA) - sin(φ)·sin(δ)] / [cos(φ)·cos(δ)]</p>
            <p>Using Zuhr values as first guess:</p>
            <p><strong>cos H₀ = [cos(${fmt(ZA_asar)}) - sin(${fmt(F11)})·sin(${fmt(sun_zuhr.dec)})] / [cos(${fmt(F11)})·cos(${fmt(sun_zuhr.dec)})]</strong></p>
            <p>cos H₀ = <strong>${cosH0.toFixed(6)}</strong> → H₀ = arccos(${cosH0.toFixed(6)}) = <strong>${H0_deg.toFixed(4)}°</strong> = <strong>${H0_hours.toFixed(4)} hours</strong></p>
            
            <h4>Step 4: First Estimate of Asar Time (t₁)</h4>
            <p class="formula">t = 12 + TZ - λ/15 - EOT + H</p>
            <p>t₁ = 12 + ${ST} - ${F13}/15 - ${fmt(sun_zuhr.eot)} + ${H0_hours.toFixed(4)}<br>
            = <strong>${t1.toFixed(4)} hours</strong></p>
            
            <h4>Step 5: Iteration 1 – Update Sun's Position at t₁</h4>
            <p>At t₁, we recalculate δ and EOT:</p>
            <p>δ₁ = <strong>${fmt(sun1.dec)}°</strong>, EOT₁ = <strong>${fmt(sun1.eot)} h</strong></p>
            <p><strong>cos H₁ = [cos(${fmt(ZA_asar)}) - sin(${fmt(F11)})·sin(${fmt(sun1.dec)})] / [cos(${fmt(F11)})·cos(${fmt(sun1.dec)})]</strong></p>
            <p>cos H₁ = <strong>${cosH1.toFixed(6)}</strong> → H₁ = <strong>${H1_deg.toFixed(4)}°</strong> = <strong>${H1_hours.toFixed(4)} hours</strong></p>
            <p>t₂ = 12 + ${ST} - ${F13}/15 - ${fmt(sun1.eot)} + ${H1_hours.toFixed(4)}<br>
            = <strong>${t2.toFixed(4)} hours</strong></p>
            
            <h4>Step 6: Iteration 2 – Final Convergence</h4>
            <p>At t₂, δ₂ = <strong>${fmt(sun2.dec)}°</strong>, EOT₂ = <strong>${fmt(sun2.eot)} h</strong></p>
            <p><strong>cos H₂ = [cos(${fmt(ZA_asar)}) - sin(${fmt(F11)})·sin(${fmt(sun2.dec)})] / [cos(${fmt(F11)})·cos(${fmt(sun2.dec)})]</strong></p>
            <p>cos H₂ = <strong>${cosH2.toFixed(6)}</strong> → H₂ = <strong>${H2_deg.toFixed(4)}°</strong> = <strong>${H2_hours.toFixed(4)} hours</strong></p>
            <p>t₃ = 12 + ${ST} - ${F13}/15 - ${fmt(sun2.eot)} + ${H2_hours.toFixed(4)}<br>
            = <strong>${t3.toFixed(4)} hours</strong></p>
            
            <h4>Step 7: Convert to Local Clock Time</h4>
            <p>t₃ = ${t3.toFixed(4)} hours = ${finalTime}</p>
            <p>Thus the Asar time is <strong>${finalTime}</strong>.</p>
            <div style="text-align: right; margin-top: 15px;">
    <button class="copy-btn" onclick="copyCalculationText(this)">Copy</button>
</div>
        </div>
    `;
}

        function getMaghribSteps() {
    let { C5, D5, E5, F11, F13, ST, elev } = readInputs();
    let date = new Date(Date.UTC(E5, D5-1, C5, 0,0,0));
