            <p>Dip = (58.2/3600)·√elev = <strong>${fmt(dip,6)}°</strong></p>
            
            <h4>Step 1: Obtain Sun's Position at Solar Noon (JD₀)</h4>
            <p>At solar noon, we obtain:</p>
            <p>δ₀ = <strong>${fmt(dec0)}°</strong><br>
            EOT₀ = <strong>${fmt(eot0)} hours</strong><br>
