             <tr><td>Ecliptic Latitude (β)</td><td>${beta.toFixed(4)}°</td></tr>
             <tr><td>True Obliquity (ε) including nutation</td><td>${epsilon.toFixed(4)}°</td></tr>
         </table>

        <h4>Conversion Formula</h4>
        <p style="font-family: monospace;">
            sin(Dec) = sin(β)·cos(ε) + cos(β)·sin(ε)·sin(λ)<br>
            Dec = arcsin( sin(β)·cos(ε) + cos(β)·sin(ε)·sin(λ) )
        </p>

        <h4>Calculation with Current Values</h4>
        <p>We need the trigonometric values of these angles:</p>
        <table style="width:100%; border-collapse: collapse;">
             <tr><td>sin(β) = sin(${beta.toFixed(4)}°)</td><td>= <span class="value">${Math.sin(beta * dtr).toFixed(6)}</span></td></tr>
             <tr><td>cos(β) = cos(${beta.toFixed(4)}°)</td><td>= <span class="value">${Math.cos(beta * dtr).toFixed(6)}</span></td></tr>
             <tr><td>sin(λ) = sin(${lambda.toFixed(4)}°)</td><td>= <span class="value">${Math.sin(lambda * dtr).toFixed(6)}</span></td></tr>
             <tr><td>cos(ε) = cos(${epsilon.toFixed(4)}°)</td><td>= <span class="value">${Math.cos(epsilon * dtr).toFixed(6)}</span></td></tr>
             <tr><td>sin(ε) = sin(${epsilon.toFixed(4)}°)</td><td>= <span class="value">${Math.sin(epsilon * dtr).toFixed(6)}</span></td></tr>
         </table>

        <p><strong>Now plug into the formula:</strong></p>
        <p style="margin-left:20px;">
            sin(Dec) = sin(β)·cos(ε) + cos(β)·sin(ε)·sin(λ)<br>
            = ${Math.sin(beta * dtr).toFixed(6)} × ${Math.cos(epsilon * dtr).toFixed(6)} + ${Math.cos(beta * dtr).toFixed(6)} × ${Math.sin(epsilon * dtr).toFixed(6)} × ${Math.sin(lambda * dtr).toFixed(6)}<br>
            = ${(Math.sin(beta * dtr) * Math.cos(epsilon * dtr)).toFixed(6)} + ${(Math.cos(beta * dtr) * Math.sin(epsilon * dtr) * Math.sin(lambda * dtr)).toFixed(6)}<br>
            = <span class="value">${sinDec.toFixed(6)}</span>
        </p>
        <p style="margin-left:20px;">
            Dec (radians) = arcsin( ${sinDec.toFixed(6)} ) = <span class="value">${dec_rad.toFixed(6)} rad</span>
        </p>
        <p style="margin-left:20px;">
            Dec (degrees) = ${dec_rad.toFixed(6)} × 180/π = <span class="value">${dec_deg.toFixed(4)}°</span>
        </p>

        <h4>Final Result (from Almanac)</h4>
        <p style="font-size:1.2rem; font-weight:bold;">
            Dec = ${formatDMS(dec_almanac)}
        </p>
        <p><i>Note: The almanac value is the definitive result; the step-by-step calculation demonstrates the underlying conversion from ecliptic to equatorial coordinates.</i></p>
    `;
}

