             <tr><td>ΔT (Delta T)</td><td>${dt.toFixed(2)} sec</td></tr>
         </table>

        <h4>Step-by-Step Calculation</h4>

        <p><strong>Step 1:</strong> Compute days and centuries since J2000.0 (JD 2451545.0).</p>
        <p>Days since J2000.0 = JD - 2451545.0 = ${JD.toFixed(5)} - 2451545.0 = <span class="value">${daysSinceJ2000.toFixed(5)}</span></p>
        <p>Centuries since J2000.0 (T) = Days / 36525 = ${daysSinceJ2000.toFixed(5)} / 36525 = <span class="value">${T.toFixed(8)}</span></p>

        <p><strong>Step 2:</strong> Compute Greenwich Mean Sidereal Time (GMST).</p>
        <p style="font-family: monospace;">
            GMST (degrees) = 280.46061837 + 360.98564736629 × (JD - 2451545.0) + 0.000387933 × T² - T³/38710000
        </p>
        <p>GMST = 280.46061837 + 360.98564736629 × ${daysSinceJ2000.toFixed(5)} + 0.000387933 × (${T.toFixed(8)})² - (${T.toFixed(8)})³/38710000</p>
        <p>GMST = <span class="value">${GMST.toFixed(6)}°</span></p>

        <p><strong>Step 3:</strong> Compute the Equation of Equinoxes due to nutation.</p>
