        <p>ε (true obliquity) = <span class="value">${eps.toFixed(6)}°</span></p>
        <p>cos(ε) = cos(${eps.toFixed(6)}°) = <span class="value">${cosd(eps).toFixed(6)}</span></p>
        <p>Equation of Equinoxes = Δψ × cos(ε) = ${delta_psi.toFixed(6)} × ${cosd(eps).toFixed(6)} = <span class="value">${eq_eq.toFixed(6)}°</span></p>

        <p><strong>Step 4:</strong> Greenwich Apparent Sidereal Time (GAST) = GMST + Equation of Equinoxes.</p>
        <p>GAST = ${GMST.toFixed(6)}° + ${eq_eq.toFixed(6)}° = <span class="value">${GAST.toFixed(6)}°</span></p>

        <p><strong>Step 5:</strong> GHA Aries = GAST (by definition).</p>
        <p>GHA Aries = <span class="value">${ghaAries_calc.toFixed(6)}°</span></p>

        <h4>Final Result (from Almanac)</h4>
        <p style="font-size:1.2rem; font-weight:bold;">
            GHA Aries = ${formatDMS(ghaAries)}
        </p>
        <p><i>Note: The almanac value is the definitive result; the step-by-step calculation demonstrates the underlying method.</i></p>
    `;
}

